"Fairy Tail" is an anime series based on the manga of the same name written by Hiro Mashima. The series is directed by Shinji Ishihara, written by Masashi Sogo, and animated by A-1 Pictures and Satelight. It began broadcasting in Japan on TV Tokyo on October 12, 2009 and is currently airing its fourth year. As of November 20, 2012, 168 episodes have aired, spanning 4 seasons. The series follows the adventures of the wizard Lucy Heartfilia after she joins the Fairy Tail wizards' guild and partners with Natsu Dragneel, who is searching for the dragon Igneel.
The series uses 28 different pieces of theme music: 14 opening themes and 14 ending themes. Several CDs containing the theme music and other tracks have been released by Pony Canyon. The first DVD compilation was released on January 29, 2010, with individual volumes being released monthly. The Southeast Asian network Animax Asia aired part of the series locally initially in English and later Japanese.
In 2011, Funimation Entertainment licensed the first season for an English-language release in North America. The Funimation-dubbed episodes aired on the Funimation Channel. The first DVD set, containing 12 episodes, was released on November 22, 2011. Similarly sized sets followed with four sets released as of March 20, 2012.
